{
  "_comment": "Category buckets for augment ids, classified from real Data Dragon tft-augments.json name+description text (457 non-tutorial augments, 2026-07-03). Only economy is currently consumed by any checker (AUGMENT_001, src/coach/checkers/augments.ts) — combat/items/units were unused placeholders until this pass, now filled with the same rigor for whenever a rule needs them. Classification method: units = augment text grants a specific named champion (cross-referenced against all champion names bundled in Data Dragon tft-champion.json across every set, not just the local Set 17 roster, since Data Dragon bundles historical/recycled augment+champion content together); items = augment text grants a specific named item (cross-referenced against real item names in data/core/items.json, restricted to ids containing the canonical _Item_ segment — items.json turned out to contain a lot of non-equippable noise: TFT_Assist_/MarketOffering gold-and-cost reward tokens, debug items, trait-activator tokens, this pass excludes all of that) or uses generic item-grant language (component/anvil/emblem/artifact/radiant item/reforger); combat = grants a raw combat stat (Attack Damage/AP/Attack Speed/Health/Armor/MR/Crit/Omnivamp/etc) with no champion or item grant. Excluded entirely from all three buckets: ids already in economy, and Set 17 god/hex/realm/blessing/ascension mechanic augments (including the *_GodAugment_* subsystem) since those are a separate drafted-per-game-state mechanic, not a normal augment pool entry. Many real augments (~100) are intentionally left unclassified because they grant generic random rewards (random champion, random component, gold, XP) that do not cleanly fit any one bucket — that is a correct outcome, not a gap. 2026-07-11 follow-up pass: found via real-ledger audit (13/51 real picks across 19 matches were uncategorized) that economy's actual boundary, confirmed against existing entries' real descriptions (Survivor/CalledShot/GoldForDummies grant literal gold; Commander_RollingForDays grants only free rerolls with no gold), is 'grants real spendable gold and/or shop rerolls' — not yet stated explicitly above. Added on that basis: PatienceIsAVirtue, Waverider, HeroicGrabBag, ExclusiveCustomization (reroll and/or literal gold grants) to economy; ItemSpiritVisage (grants TFT_Item_Redemption, a real named item) to items. Left unclassified per the existing 'generic random reward' rule above (verified, not skipped): ExplosiveGrowth (XP only, not gold), PowerUp (raises next augment's tier, no gold/item/champion/stat grant), BoosterPackPlusPlus and Expedition and AuraFarming (grant a random/generic-tier champion, not one specific named champion — same shape as the already-excluded 'random champion' case), Calltochaos (explicitly 'a powerful and random reward').",
